dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: common_instrument_attributes
class.description: Attributes that describe instrument characteristics such as times, temperatures, voltages or pressures that are common to more than one instrument aboard the OSIRIS-REx Spacecraft.

class.title: data_processing_information
class.description: This class contains the data processing information for a specific observation or set of observations. Items included in this class include names of input files used in the data processing, the source (test or flight) of the data, who or where the data was processed, and if necessary software names and version numbers.

class.title: data_quality
class.description: This class contains data quality information for a specific observation or set of observations. Attributes can include data quality flags, as well as checksum status.

class.title: instrument_telemetry_identification
class.description: This class contains the spacecraft telemetry packet type identification information for a specific observation or set of observations.

class.title: mission_information
class.description: This class contains information about the OSIRIS-REx mission and mission phases. The attributes in this class are common to all mission data products.

class.title: ocm_image_properties
class.description: This class contains the OSIRIS-REx Camera Suite (OCAMS) image properties. Attributes specify the type of image taken for the specific observation.

class.title: ocm_instrument_attributes
class.description: This class contains instrument attributes specific to the OSIRIS-REx Camera Suite (OCAMS). These instrument attributes are such items as instrument set-up parameters for each image or sequence of images taken, instrument temperatures, voltages and currents, or other parameters recorded by the instrument on an image by image basis.

class.title: spatial
class.description: This class contains spatial information for a specific observation or set of observations that is not otherwise found in the GEOMETRY Discipline Dictionary. Attributes included may be ancillary World Coordinate System (WCS) values or additional quaternion information that should be used with caution.

class.title: tcm_instrument_attributes
class.description: This class contains instrument attributes specific to the OSIRIS-REx Navigation Camera (TagCam). These instrument attributes are such items as instrument set-up parameters for each image or sequence of images taken, instrument temperatures or other parameters recorded by the instrument on an image by image basis.

class.title: time
class.description: This class contains timing information for a specific observation or set of observations. This class is a mission type class meaning that the timing values given in this class have been calculated using standard SPICE libraries and the appropriate mission specific SPICE kernels based on the instrument specific spacecraft clock values recorded at the time of the observation.

attribute.title: bennana
attribute.description: Azimuth of the North polar Axis of the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu), positive from the +NAXIS2 direction toward the +NAXIS1 direction; see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value; assumes undistorted optics; will be -999 if the calculation fails
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: bennu_dec
attribute.description: Declination of the vector, expressed in the Earth Mean Equator of the J2000 Epoch, from the ORX spacecraft toward the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: bennu_naxis1_offset
attribute.description: Approximate offset from CRPIX1 pixel in +NAXIS1 direction of the location of the center of the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value; assumes undistorted optics

attribute.title: bennu_naxis2_offset
attribute.description: Approximate offset from CRPIX2 pixel in +NAXIS2 direction of the location of the center of the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value; assumes undistorted optics

attribute.title: bennu_ra
attribute.description: Right Ascension of the vector, expressed in the Earth Mean Equator of the J2000 Epoch, from the ORX spacecraft toward the target named in FITS keyword BENNURDT (typically Bennu); see also BENNURDQ for a statement of the quality of this value
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: bennu_radec_quality
attribute.description: (Quality: provenance) for the BENNURA, BENNUDEC, BENNUNX1, BENNUNX2 FITS keywords. This will be one of three values: (BEST: SPK), meaning the geometry was obtained from SPICE SP-Kernels; (POOR: osculating elements; +/-1E6km), meaning the geometry was obtained from osculating orbital elements of Bennu w.r.t the Sun, and will have uncertainties of order 1E6km; (NONE: FAILURE), meaning both the SPK and elements methods failed; the parentheses, (), are only delimiters here and not part of the quality:provenance values.

attribute.title: bennu_radec_target
attribute.description: Target for the BENNURA, BENNUDEC, BENNUNX1 and BENNUNX2 FTIS keywords; typically BENNU; may be NONE if the calculation failed. Target is not required to be in the field of view.

attribute.description: Phase Angle. The angle between the vector pointing to the Sun and the vector pointing to the Spacecraft. If Boresight Flag NE 1, then value shall be -9999. Allowed range is 0.0 to 180.0
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: radesys
attribute.description: International Celestial Reference System (ICRS)

attribute.title: range
attribute.description: Range from S/C to boresight intersection
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: right_ascension
attribute.description: Boresight Right Ascension (RA) in J2000 frame
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: sc2sun_phi_deg
attribute.description: Phi component (angle from XY plane, positive toward +Z) of spherical coordinate system vector, pointing from the ORX spacecraft toward the Sun, in the ORX_SPACECRAFT frame
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: sc2sun_range_km
attribute.description: Range component of spherical coordinate system vector, pointing from the ORX spacecraft toward the Sun, in the ORX_SPACECRAFT frame
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: sc2sun_theta_deg
attribute.description: Theta component (angle around +Z from XZ plane, positive from +X toward +Y) of spherical coordinate system vector, pointing from the ORX spacecraft toward the Sun, in the ORX_SPACECRAFT frame
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: sc2sun_uvx
attribute.description: X component of Cartesian coordinate system unit vector, pointing from the ORX spacecraft toward the Sun, in the ORX_SPACECRAFT frame

attribute.title: sc2sun_uvy
attribute.description: Y component of Cartesian coordinate system unit vector, pointing from the ORX spacecraft toward the Sun, in the ORX_SPACECRAFT frame

attribute.title: sc2sun_uvz
attribute.description: Z component of Cartesian coordinate system unit vector, pointing from the ORX spacecraft toward the Sun, in the ORX_SPACECRAFT frame

attribute.title: semimajor_axis
attribute.description: Semimajor axis of FOV ellipse on surface
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: semiminor_axis
attribute.description: Semiminor axis of FOV ellipse on surface
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: sun_range
attribute.description: Range from Sun to center of Bennu
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: sunbeamr
attribute.description: Range to Sun from SunBEAM target
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: sunbeams
attribute.description: Status of SunBEAM calculation, will be either SUCCESS or FAILURE

attribute.title: sunbeamt
attribute.description: Target for SunBEAM quantities; will be one of Bennu, Earth, And Moon; if observation target is not Earth or Moon, then this will be BENNU

attribute.title: sunbeamx
attribute.description: J2000 X-component of vector to Sun from SunBEAM target
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: sunbeamy
attribute.description: J2000 Y-component of vector to Sun from SunBEAM target
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: sunbeamz
attribute.description: J2000 Z-component of vector to Sun from SunBEAM target
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: target_range
attribute.description: Range from S/C to target body center
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: att_rate_x
attribute.description: The x-axis component of the spacecraft angular momentum rate in spacecraft body frame at the ATT_TIME

attribute.title: att_rate_y
attribute.description: The y-axis component of the spacecraft angular momentum rate in spacecraft body frame at the ATT_TIME

attribute.title: att_rate_z
attribute.description: The z-axis component of the spacecraft angular momentum rate in spacecraft body frame at the ATT_TIME

attribute.title: att_time
attribute.description: The spacecraft clock time when attitude data was collected

attribute.title: bpp
attribute.description: Records the pixel depth of the transmitted image. If the image was initially acquired as 12 bits, then it can be sent as 12 bits or 8 bits. If the image was initially acquired as 8 bits, then this value is ignored and the output is always 8 bits. The companding mode is only significant if companding is turned on. Keyword may be blank if the transmit-image-raw command was used to acquire image.

attribute.title: camera_head_temp
attribute.description: Camera head temperature in digital number (if available).

attribute.title: gain
attribute.description: The sensor analog gain value to use. Legal values are 8-31 and 40-63. Values from 8 to 31 specify gains in the range 1 to 3.875 in steps of 0.125; values from 40 to 63 specify gain in the range 2 to 7.75 in steps of 0.25. Gains in the range [2, 4) should be commanded using the first range

attribute.title: image_len
attribute.description: Recorded image length

attribute.title: image_size_estimate
attribute.description: initial size estimate for image in flash

attribute.title: img_cmd_cam
attribute.description: Specifies which camera to use. Legal values are 1 (for both DVR-4s) and 2 (for the DVR-4 with StowCam attached).

attribute.title: img_cmd_compress
attribute.description: Take image hardware image compression mode. 0 means no compression; 0xff means lossless compression; 1-99 means JPEG compression quality N, 4:2:2 color subsampling if applicable; 101-199 means JPEG compression quality N, 4:4:4 color subsampling if applicable. Hardware compression is only available in 8-bit mode; if companding is turned off, this value must be 0.

attribute.title: img_cmd_exp
attribute.description: The commanded 16-bit exposure time for each image. For values from 0 to 5000, exposure time is in units of 0.1 msec, providing exposures of 0 to 0.5 seconds. From 5001 to 65535, exposure time is in units of 0.5msec with an offset of 0.5 seconds, so that the maximum exposure time is 0.5e-3*(65535-5000)+0.5 equals 30.7675 seconds.

attribute.title: img_cmd_gain
attribute.description: The sensor analog gain value. Legal values are 8-31 and 40-63. Values from 8 to 31 specify gains in the range 1 to 3.875 in steps of 0.125; values from 40 to 63 specify gain in the range 2 to 7.75 in steps of 0.25. Gains in the range (2, 4) are commanded using the first range

attribute.title: img_cmd_h
attribute.description: The starting height of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

attribute.title: img_cmd_int
attribute.description: The 16-bit time interval between images in seconds, from 0 (as fast as possible) to 65535 seconds.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: img_cmd_mode
attribute.description: 0- 12-to-8 bit companding on/off; 1-3 companding mode (0 equals square root, 1-7 linear divide by exp2(N-1)); 4- dark pixels on/off; test pattern control (on equals 1/off equals 0); 6 enable additional sensor register settings (enable equals 1/disable equals 0); 7 reserved

attribute.title: img_cmd_num_imgs
attribute.description: The number of images to acquire in this sequence. Legal values are 1 to 255.

attribute.title: img_cmd_opcode
attribute.description: TAGCAMS Command 8-bit Operations Code (Opcode)

attribute.title: img_cmd_seq
attribute.description: The sequence identifier to assign to these images. Legal values are 1 to 255.

attribute.title: img_cmd_subsample
attribute.description: The subsampling to use when acquiring the image. Legal values for this field are 0 (no subsampling), 1 (bin 2x2), 4 (bin 4x4), and 16-23 (skip (N-14)*(N-14)).

attribute.title: img_cmd_sx
attribute.description: The starting X of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

attribute.title: img_cmd_sy
attribute.description: The starting Y of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

attribute.title: img_cmd_w
attribute.description: The starting Z of the area of the image sensor to read, in multiples of 16 pixels. If 0 is used for all values, then the full frame is read (2592x1944 pixels with dark pixels off, 2752x2004 pixels with dark pixels on.) Reading outside the bounds of the image array is illegal.

attribute.title: powered_on_dvr
attribute.description: Touch and Go Camera Suite Powered On Digital Video Recorder: 0 equals TAGCAMS_DVR_1, 1 equals TAGCAMS_DVR_2

attribute.title: quaternion0
attribute.description: Spacecraft quaternion in J2000 (q0 equals cos(t/2)) obtained at the ATT_TIME. Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image. SPICE quaternion standard is that Q0 is the scalar value which is followed here.

attribute.title: quaternion1
attribute.description: Spacecraft quaternion in J2000 (q1 equals sin(theta/2) obtained at the ATT_TIME. Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image.

attribute.title: quaternion2
attribute.description: Spacecraft quaternion in J2000 (q2 equals sin(theta/2))obtained at the ATT_TIME. Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image.

attribute.title: quaternion3
attribute.description: Spacecraft quaternion in J2000 (q3 equals sin(theta/2)) obtained at the ATT_TIME. Quaternion values are telemetry values based on the ATT_TIME parameter and may differ from the SPICE calculated quaternions at mid-observation time by several seconds. This value is to be used with caution as the timing many not be for the boresight of the corresponding image.

attribute.title: seconds
attribute.description: TAGCAMS Mini Header spacecraft clock time in seconds. The spacecraft clock time tag is the start of exposure for line 1 of the image plus or minus 0.1 seconds.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: sequence_id
attribute.description: TAGCAMS commanded sequence identifier

attribute.title: spare
attribute.description: Spare

attribute.title: subseconds
attribute.description: TAGCAMS Mini Header spacecraft clock time in sub-seconds. The spacecraft clock time tag is the start of exposure for line 1 of the image plus or minus 0.1 seconds.!important
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: trans_cmd_compression
attribute.description: Compression mode. 0 means no compression; 0xff means lossless compression; 1-99 means JPEG compression quality N, grayscale; 101-199 means JPEG compression quality N, 4:2:2 color subsampling. JPEG compression can only be applied to 8-bit data. Note that if a color camera image is compressed as grayscale, compression efficiency may be degraded. Keyword may be blank if the transmit-image-raw command was used to acquire image.

attribute.title: trans_cmd_summing
attribute.description: Turns 2x2 summing on or off. Legal values are 1 (no summing) and 2 (2x2 summing.) Summing can only be applied to 8-bit data. Images with both compression and summing selected will be compressed but not summed. Keyword may be blank if the transmit-image-raw command was used to acquire image.

attribute.title: date_of_observation
attribute.description: Observation start time in UTC (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sss)

attribute.title: delta_obs
attribute.description: Delta between mid-observation time and spacecraft clock string (Mid-observation time) - (SCLK_STR timestamp), in seconds used to verify exposure time.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: effective_exposure
attribute.description: The effective exposure time after charge smear removal

attribute.title: expo_ms
attribute.description: Exposure time in milliseconds
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: exposec
attribute.description: Exposure time in seconds
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: exposure
attribute.description: Exposure time in seconds
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: ground_receipt_time
attribute.description: Ground Receive Time in UTC (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sss)

attribute.title: int_time
attribute.description: Commanded exposure time in milliseconds
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: mid_obs
attribute.description: Spacecraft mid-exposure time, UTC [Cal d] (DATE_OBS - .5*EXPTIME).

attribute.title: mid_obs_et
attribute.description: The ephemeris time of the mid-exposure time, mid_obs
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, ns, s, yr

attribute.title: mid_obs_sclk
attribute.description: The SCLK string of the mid-exposure time, mid_obs

attribute.title: sclk_string
attribute.description: Spacecraft Clock String at start of image observation

attribute.title: spoc_date
attribute.description: Coordinated Universal Time file was created by SPOC (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sss).

attribute.title: start_sclk
attribute.description: SCLK Time (#/SSSSSSSSSS.sssss) of the first frame in the science sequence.

attribute.title: stop_sclk
attribute.description: SCLK Time (#/SSSSSSSSSS.sssss) of the last record in the science sequence

attribute.title: utc
attribute.description: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sss observation start
